outputs.output_descr: Relevant ministries and subnational government agencies in target provinces have the necessary financial and human resources, technical expertise, and mechanisms to implement and coordinate the National Strategy on Access to Justice.

SAJI is a new umbrella project on access to justice.  There are 5 (five) objectives of the project.  At the end of the project, BAPPENAS and UNDP aim to see more Indonesians, particularly women and vulnerable groups as indigenous and forest-dependant communities have better access to high quality and effective dispute resolution and grievance handling mechanisms through state as well as non-state mechanisms.
